11/01/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- In a statement Thursday (January 10th), US Under Secretary of State Nicholas Burns congratulated new Kosovo Prime Minister Hashim Thaci and President Fatmir Sejdiu on the formation of a governing coalition. Thaci took office at a ceremony Thursday after receiving approval from parliament, which also gave Sejdiu a new five-year mandate. Burns also welcomed recent commitments by the leaders to respect the rights of the Serb population and other minorities. (Kosovalive, RTK, RFE, Balkanweb, Telegrafi, UPI - 10/01/08)
